-- Citigroup bonds gain on capital injection
-- 
-- Tue Nov 27, 2007 8:54am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/11/27/us-citi-corporate-bonds-idUSN2746972520071127

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Bonds of Citigroup Inc ( C.N ) gained after the largest U.S. bank said it is selling up to 4.9 percent of itself for $7.5 billion to the Gulf Arab emirate of Abu Dhabi. 

 The spread for Citigroup's 6.125 percent notes due in 2017 narrowed by 20 basis points on Tuesday to 185 basis points over U.S. Treasuries, according to MarketAxess data.  (Reporting by  Walden Siew )